WEBVTT

00:31.330 --> 00:32.031
Well, good morning.

00:32.171 --> 00:34.114
So great to see each and every one of you.

00:34.175 --> 00:35.216
Thanks for being here.

00:35.276 --> 00:38.862
And if you're a guest, a special welcome.

00:38.902 --> 00:41.967
And for all of you who fought through the traffic, thank you for that.

00:41.987 --> 00:56.189
I never get over the fact that in a world that seems to be taking a big exit away from God, we get to be a part of a church where people sit in traffic jams to hear about Jesus and grow.

00:56.229 --> 00:59.154
It's really a phenomenal opportunity.

00:59.970 --> 01:02.353
And you and your invites make that happen.

01:02.473 --> 01:09.201
And you saw in the video bumper that we're continuing in this series based upon the question, what if it's true?

01:10.062 --> 01:10.763
What if it's true?

01:11.824 --> 01:17.852
And you saw that this week's conversation is on what if it's true failure is not final?

01:19.093 --> 01:26.121
Which is really the foundational motivation of my entire life, that particular truth.

01:26.983 --> 01:29.906
In fact, someone I was talking to backstage said,

01:30.114 --> 01:41.294
They've been coming here 30 years and they said the two things that you've consistently really reminded us of, your entire ministry here have been failures not final and we can expect God's best.

01:41.354 --> 01:44.319
And I tell you, those aren't bad things to be known for right there.

01:44.680 --> 01:46.744
So we're glad that you're here.

01:46.804 --> 01:54.898
And we wanted to start out, we wanted to start out even before I came out on this platform to lead in this conversation.

01:55.106 --> 01:58.111
we wanted to show you that failure's not final.

01:58.251 --> 02:10.009
And so we allowed a person who has no abilities whatsoever to give Northridge news to be on video talking it, but failure's not final.

02:10.069 --> 02:11.892
In fact, failure is a prerequisite here.

02:12.032 --> 02:15.878
If I'm going to be the pastor of this church, everybody's got to suck to be here.

02:15.978 --> 02:18.642
It's like, and some of you are going, you've already failed.

02:18.662 --> 02:19.363
You said suck.

02:19.383 --> 02:19.924
There you go.

02:19.964 --> 02:21.426
Failure's not final.

02:21.794 --> 02:24.016
But actually, Marissa did a great job.

02:24.437 --> 02:28.200
Just so you know, a lot of people say, wow, you wrote that script and it made her look up.

02:28.220 --> 02:29.321
We didn't write that script.

02:29.361 --> 02:30.362
She's just that bad.

02:30.483 --> 02:31.524
I'm just telling you right now.

02:32.445 --> 02:34.266
But failure is not final.

02:36.529 --> 02:45.698
All right, I have to tell you that particular catchphrase, that particular idea, that particular truth really does motivate me.

02:45.758 --> 02:50.162
But a lot of people here would have a hard time believing

02:50.722 --> 02:59.672
that that particular truth is so important to me, because let's be honest, this is how you see me, and this is how you know me today.

02:59.772 --> 03:16.530
Even if you're a first-time guest at Northridge right now, I'm standing on the platform of what seems to be a fairly successful church, and I've been here a long time, and so boy, I must be a pretty good guy, but you need to know that's nonsense.

03:17.474 --> 03:30.555
That's absolutely an illusion created by the context, the environment that we're in, the privilege that I've been given to not only be a Jesus follower, but to get to talk about Jesus in a place like this.

03:30.815 --> 03:32.398
I need you to know.

03:32.418 --> 03:37.045
I need to somehow try and open the vest.

03:37.125 --> 03:42.834
I need to somehow shatter the perception that apart from God's grace,

03:43.650 --> 03:48.838
I would be seen and known in a very different way than you perceive me right now.

03:49.519 --> 03:51.802
One word would do it, failure.

03:53.405 --> 03:53.825
Failure.

03:54.687 --> 04:00.515
And I have to tell you, this isn't just humble pastoral hyperbole.

04:01.697 --> 04:09.128
You know where we exaggerate, how messed up we are, so other people will think we're just like them, so they'll listen to us.

04:09.148 --> 04:10.630
That's not what this is.

04:10.971 --> 04:13.074
This is the fact.

04:13.730 --> 04:16.413
of my life from the past.

04:17.214 --> 04:21.639
Apart from God's grace, failure is my only foundation.

04:21.659 --> 04:23.981
And I'll start with a dramatic example.

04:24.262 --> 04:28.787
Anyone who's been a part of Northridge for a long time has heard this, but I only have one story to tell.

04:28.887 --> 04:35.294
And I just, I need everyone to know that failure is something that I don't just relate to.

04:35.374 --> 04:42.642
It's something that really was the epitome of who I was and still can be who I am.

04:43.458 --> 04:49.444
I was, as a teenager, kicked out of high school twice.

04:49.464 --> 04:57.892
Now, I'm not talking about the cheap version where you get suspended for three days, you have a nice little vacation, you go back and you get to brag about it for the rest of your life.

04:58.333 --> 05:05.980
I mean, expelled, kicked out, can't go back twice in high school, kicked out.

05:06.701 --> 05:11.986
And you'd think because, you know, you're probably like this, you go, okay.

05:12.706 --> 05:19.033
Learn that lesson, bad way to go, but I'm not a two baseball bad guy.

05:19.113 --> 05:20.915
I'm a multiple baseball bad guy.

05:20.935 --> 05:24.238
I need to learn it over and over and over again.

05:24.338 --> 05:32.487
I didn't grow up, I didn't learn my lesson, and so I went on to college and I got kicked out of college twice.

05:34.269 --> 05:39.034
And I don't know what it is about me and the number two, but one's not enough.

05:39.735 --> 05:42.578
I've got to obsess and go further than that, right?

05:42.754 --> 05:50.706
So, now what I need you to do is I need you to process this from a point of reality.

05:52.869 --> 05:53.630
Think about this.

05:53.650 --> 05:56.835
If you are a parent, it won't be hard for you to get there.

05:56.895 --> 06:11.858
Many who come here aren't yet parents, or never will be, but if you're a parent, you can, I'm sure, relate a little bit with, empathize a little bit with,

06:12.130 --> 06:21.503
Imagine a little bit with my parents in their disappointment and the agony of the experience I caused them.

06:22.484 --> 06:36.783
And I have to tell you, I'm a parent of now three adult children whom I love profoundly and though they weren't perfect, I'm telling you, I don't know why, but I didn't have to experience with them what my parents experienced with me.

06:37.044 --> 06:39.026
I mean, I was a mess.

06:39.427 --> 06:41.650
Simply put, from early on,

06:41.826 --> 06:43.808
I was a spectacular failure.

06:45.389 --> 06:50.654
It was my one natural talent, to be honest with you.

06:50.674 --> 06:52.376
And it wasn't limited to my school years.

06:52.736 --> 06:55.639
I wish I could say, oh, after that college thing.

06:57.060 --> 06:58.182
Done with stupid stuff.

06:58.302 --> 06:59.102
No, I wasn't.

07:01.064 --> 07:07.450
The reality is that my failures have been many and often, big and small, in every area of my life.

07:08.692 --> 07:11.314
And it's the reason, really, that I have such

07:11.522 --> 07:18.972
a heart for those who have or are right now experiencing significant failure in their lives.

07:20.414 --> 07:21.876
It's because I can relate.

07:21.937 --> 07:31.470
But what I'm going to share this weekend is the wonderful truth that changed my life forever.

07:32.792 --> 07:40.242
This, in fact, is the truth that has made my entire life possible, my marriage

07:40.322 --> 07:43.367
my ministry possible.

07:43.387 --> 07:49.617
It's given me hope after all my failures and I need you to know it can do the same for you.

07:49.657 --> 07:57.970
So I'm not telling you as one who's untouched by failure how you can stop being such a failure.

07:58.410 --> 08:08.306
I'm here as a failure to share with you that you don't have to be defined by that word or that reality.

08:09.090 --> 08:13.795
Here's the truth that we're talking about this weekend.

08:14.776 --> 08:20.362
God is willing and able to forgive our failures.

08:21.823 --> 08:25.307
God is willing and able to forgive our failures.

08:25.567 --> 08:28.190
And both sides of that equation are very important.

08:29.371 --> 08:36.498
It would be worthless if God was willing to forgive our failures, but wasn't able to.

08:38.306 --> 08:59.753
It would be worthless if God was able to forgive our failures, but wasn't willing to, but profoundly, and for a reason beyond my ability to explain, God is not just able to forgive our failures, he's willing to forgive our failures, which means our failures don't have to be final.

09:00.493 --> 09:04.438
And this is the truth, really, of all of scripture, from beginning to end.

09:04.699 --> 09:07.442
So many people misunderstand what

09:07.810 --> 09:09.152
Scripture is teaching.

09:09.432 --> 09:12.436
It's teaching you that your failures don't have to be final.

09:12.716 --> 09:14.358
You're in good company as a failure.

09:16.661 --> 09:17.382
That's what it's teaching.

09:18.783 --> 09:28.895
And I, instead of giving you a bunch of verses to start off with, we'll certainly get to those, but I want to give you an example of a human being whom you should be able to relate to.

09:29.076 --> 09:29.897
I certainly can.

09:31.278 --> 09:32.179
His name's Peter.

09:33.581 --> 09:34.322
Peter

09:34.466 --> 09:50.630
is known as an apostle of Jesus Christ, one of the pillars and foundational followers of Jesus in the early days, one of the ones that ultimately is the reason that we can know about the love and grace of Jesus Christ.

09:50.711 --> 09:53.054
It's through this guy named Peter.

09:53.415 --> 09:57.120
He's a big deal in Christianity.

09:58.382 --> 10:03.570
The only problem is as a human, he was a spectacular failure.

10:04.962 --> 10:08.568
You can read through the Scripture, and it's like, I love how honest the Bible is.

10:09.009 --> 10:10.672
Peter was a mess.

10:10.973 --> 10:17.344
He was an arrogant, egotistical, self-confident mess.

10:18.446 --> 10:23.776
And you can see it all the way through his story, but the story I want you to see is in Luke 22.

10:24.457 --> 10:29.426
And you can read it on your own, but it's the place where Jesus tells Peter

10:29.538 --> 10:40.574
I'm telling you right now, in spite of your big words to the contrary, you're going to deny me three times before the rooster crows after the morning I've been betrayed.

10:41.536 --> 10:43.158
You're gonna deny me three times spectacular.

10:43.398 --> 10:56.818
And this was in the wake, if you read all of the gospels, of Peter going, I love you more than all these other guys that say they love you, and I'm more committed than all these other guys that say they're committed to you, and I'll sacrifice my very life

10:56.930 --> 11:00.194
I'll go to prison and die to follow you."

11:00.214 --> 11:03.960
And Jesus said, no you don't and no you won't.

11:06.723 --> 11:12.731
You're going to deny me three times before the rooster crows.

11:12.751 --> 11:13.653
And Peter didn't buy it.

11:13.733 --> 11:14.494
Peter didn't believe him.

11:14.714 --> 11:16.116
But you'll never guess what happened.

11:18.599 --> 11:26.450
In spite of his big words, his self-proclaimed confidence, Peter denied Jesus three times.

11:27.586 --> 11:30.269
and then the rooster crowed.

11:30.289 --> 11:32.931
So devastating moment, I mean devastating moment for him.

11:34.893 --> 11:38.216
In Luke 22, you can see how Jesus looked at him at that moment.

11:39.237 --> 11:41.079
And he saw Jesus and he collapsed.

11:41.539 --> 11:48.926
He caved the guilt, the shame, the regret, the self-realization of his failure.

11:49.907 --> 11:50.928
It was huge.

11:54.552 --> 11:57.074
But what's interesting in Luke 22 is that

11:57.730 --> 12:08.423
Jesus, in the introduction to telling Peter, he was going to deny him three times, says something very interesting, profound, at least for me.

12:08.443 --> 12:11.847
I want you to see it in Luke chapter 22 verse 32.

12:11.887 --> 12:23.922
This is before, just before, in the same chapter, he says, you're gonna deny me three times, you're gonna mess up, you're gonna be, oh, it says, Jesus talking, but I have prayed for you, Simon, that your faith may not fail.

12:26.722 --> 12:31.488
And when you have turned back to me, strengthen your brothers.

12:33.390 --> 12:34.731
He's talking about the betrayal.

12:34.791 --> 12:36.333
He's talking about the denials.

12:39.317 --> 12:43.702
And I don't know if you see this, but Jesus wasn't saying, God, don't let him deny me three times.

12:44.022 --> 12:46.285
Jesus knew he was going to deny him three times.

12:49.789 --> 12:54.354
Jesus was praying that his faith wouldn't fail because Jesus knew in the end

12:54.722 --> 12:59.988
The only thing that could rescue him from being a forever failure was his faith.

13:02.190 --> 13:05.614
I'm praying that your faith won't fail because I'm telling you, you're gonna fall away.

13:05.895 --> 13:09.579
And when you've turned back, strengthen your brothers.

13:10.260 --> 13:11.721
Now we'll come back to that again and again.

13:11.761 --> 13:14.625
And I want you to know, this isn't just for Peter, this is for us.

13:15.826 --> 13:18.249
This isn't just for his story, it's for our story.

13:19.230 --> 13:22.994
And I want you to see what Jesus is saying to us

13:23.234 --> 13:26.138
as he's saying this with clarity to Peter, okay?

13:26.379 --> 13:27.380
And so I'm gonna go through it.

13:27.641 --> 13:34.451
And I just need you to remember this is relevant for you and it should resonate with you.

13:34.511 --> 13:38.177
It's important to you or you'll never experience what God wants for you in life.

13:38.237 --> 13:42.043
Just as Peter wouldn't, certainly as I wouldn't, you need this.

13:42.083 --> 13:44.447
So I hope you'll mark it down, you'll listen.

13:44.867 --> 13:49.174
I'll try and give you a volume of these things, but I will try.

13:49.214 --> 13:51.858
And if you know me at all,

13:52.962 --> 13:57.127
You know I'm not going to succeed at not saying more than I have to say.

13:57.247 --> 14:06.017
I can say a hundred words for everyone that needs to be said, so I hope you're not hungry or you've bought a protein bar because here we go.

14:07.558 --> 14:12.124
In saying this to Peter, I actually just want to make the traffic jam worth your time.

14:12.144 --> 14:12.904
That's what it's going to be.

14:14.186 --> 14:18.431
I'm going to give you extra credit teaching today, yeah.

14:18.451 --> 14:18.871
Not really.

14:19.071 --> 14:20.473
Security, lock the doors.

14:20.533 --> 14:21.394
All right.

14:21.858 --> 14:29.407
In saying this to Peter, Jesus was making clear to us that he knows our failures before they happen.

14:32.210 --> 14:34.793
He says, Peter, before he ever said, you're going to fail.

14:35.133 --> 14:36.835
He said, I'm praying that your faith won't fail.

14:37.215 --> 14:38.557
He's just going, what are you talking about, dude?

14:38.577 --> 14:40.379
I'm going to go to prison and die for you.

14:40.399 --> 14:41.520
And he goes, huh?

14:41.540 --> 14:50.290
But when you turn back after your failure, strengthen your brothers.

14:51.010 --> 14:51.871
when you turn back.

14:53.254 --> 14:54.295
When you turn back, what's he saying?

14:55.217 --> 14:58.422
I know your failures before they happen.

14:59.845 --> 15:02.229
And this is why it's important, at least for me, maybe for you.

15:03.270 --> 15:17.554
I have to tell you, when I fail, I get all messed up and I start retreating from God and hiding from God a little bit, leaving him out of my life a little bit because I know he's absolutely

15:17.602 --> 15:20.545
I was surprised by my failure and disappointed with me.

15:20.825 --> 15:24.468
He wasn't disappointed five days ago, but now in the wake of my failure.

15:25.048 --> 15:28.632
Oh, it just shocked him that I failed and so he's disappointed.

15:28.952 --> 15:30.373
And that's where a lot of you sit.

15:30.693 --> 15:38.520
You actually think somehow you surprised God by your failure and you disappointed him and he didn't know you'd do that.

15:38.880 --> 15:42.604
And so he's now ashamed that he ever had a relationship with you.

15:42.884 --> 15:47.588
That is garbage, that is wrong, that is not true.

15:47.568 --> 15:48.929
Your failure was coming.

15:49.210 --> 15:52.693
God has loved you anyway and God still loves you today.

15:52.753 --> 15:53.654
He knows.

15:55.156 --> 16:01.122
You've got to get ahold of this or you'll never get out of the wake of your failure.

16:03.305 --> 16:04.286
He's not surprised.

16:05.147 --> 16:07.269
There are some times I go to prayer and I go, God, I don't know.

16:08.130 --> 16:12.274
I don't know if you caught it, but I just had a thought.

16:14.946 --> 16:16.789
And he's gone, I've had a thought forever.

16:16.989 --> 16:17.630
You're an idiot.

16:17.850 --> 16:20.174
You know that kind of thing.

16:20.194 --> 16:21.576
He knows our failures before they happen.

16:23.539 --> 16:30.870
In saying this to Peter, Jesus was making clear to us that he loves us even in the face of our failures.

16:32.793 --> 16:35.517
We think, oh, we've so disappointed him, he can't love me anymore.

16:35.817 --> 16:41.706
Well, oh, the last failure was a surprise to God, so he can't love you anymore.

16:42.487 --> 16:44.210
When Jesus hung on the cross,

16:45.698 --> 16:47.280
He saw you in all your failures.

16:49.644 --> 16:50.926
And He loved you enough to do what?

16:52.028 --> 16:52.709
To die for you.

16:54.331 --> 16:56.414
He loves us even in the face of our failures.

16:56.495 --> 16:58.798
Peter, I love you so much.

16:58.838 --> 16:59.639
I'm praying for you, man.

16:59.679 --> 17:01.763
I don't want your faith to fail.

17:02.964 --> 17:03.665
You're going to blow it.

17:03.686 --> 17:07.852
But when you turn back, strengthen your brothers.

17:11.317 --> 17:14.482
In this saying to Peter, Jesus was making clear to us that

17:15.074 --> 17:17.518
He prays for us in the midst of our failures.

17:18.619 --> 17:29.135
Now this is important to me because it's easier for me to pray for people I'm caring about in the moment than it is to pray for people.

17:31.458 --> 17:32.920
I want God to wipe off the planet.

17:35.324 --> 17:37.888
Is it okay to be human here or do I have to pretend with you people?

17:39.330 --> 17:40.592
Yeah.

17:40.612 --> 17:42.194
If you're too good for that comment,

17:42.626 --> 17:45.069
you belong in the fake church somewhere down the road.

17:45.169 --> 17:48.133
I mean, this is for real people, you know, okay?

17:48.493 --> 17:55.102
And I'm gonna tell you, it's easy for me to pray for people who, you know, pray for me, who like me, who are in good terms for me.

17:55.783 --> 17:58.466
Dear Jesus, bless them so they can keep blessing me.

18:00.268 --> 18:08.018
It's really difficult for me to pray, for God's goodness to be poured out on people I despise.

18:11.362 --> 18:14.465
But Jesus prays for me in the midst of my worst failures.

18:15.706 --> 18:27.818
And he prays for you in the midst of your worst failures, which means you're never so far away, no matter what you have done or will ever do, that Jesus doesn't love you enough to keep praying for you.

18:28.279 --> 18:35.126
So why are you running from the only one who keeps praying for you when my parents had a hard time praying for me?

18:37.708 --> 18:39.410
Jesus was still praying for me.

18:40.866 --> 18:41.827
and he's praying for you.

18:43.008 --> 18:46.391
Don't hide from him, don't run from him, don't dismiss him.

18:48.894 --> 19:09.234
Hebrew 725 makes it clear, not only did he tell it to Peter, but it says it straight up, therefore he is able to save completely those who come to God through him, this is talking about Jesus, because he always lives to intercede for, to stand on the gap for, to mediate for, to pray for them, wherever they're at.

19:10.146 --> 19:11.107
He's praying for you.

19:11.127 --> 19:25.145
In saying this to Peter before he betrayed Jesus three times, in saying this to him, Jesus is making clear to us today that he does not see our failures as final.

19:27.708 --> 19:32.254
Jesus didn't say, Peter, dude, you're thinking about betraying me, which he wasn't, by the way.

19:32.494 --> 19:38.642
You're thinking about betraying me, but don't do it because if you do, I can't use you anymore.

19:40.002 --> 19:41.364
You can't be one of my followers.

19:41.404 --> 19:42.746
You can't ever serve me again.

19:42.807 --> 19:43.968
Sorry, dude.

19:43.988 --> 19:46.112
Don't fail or you're done.

19:46.172 --> 19:47.634
That's not what Jesus does.

19:47.995 --> 19:49.918
Sadly, that's what we do to each other.

19:53.484 --> 19:54.025
You failed me.

19:54.065 --> 19:56.068
I have nothing left to do with you.

19:56.088 --> 19:56.989
I don't care about you anymore.

19:57.009 --> 19:58.352
I won't even pray for you anymore.

20:01.016 --> 20:01.717
But not Jesus.

20:01.857 --> 20:04.882
He does not see our failures as final.

20:05.218 --> 20:07.001
Now, I'm not saying he's not disappointed.

20:07.261 --> 20:11.488
I'm not saying he's not grieved for us, but it's for us, not for him.

20:11.528 --> 20:12.670
He's not surprised.

20:12.710 --> 20:15.033
It's for what we're missing, not what he's losing.

20:15.053 --> 20:28.754
There shouldn't be a motivation for us to fail because once again, we're losing everything when we fail, but Jesus never sees us as final, and too many of us are living like it's done.

20:28.815 --> 20:31.839
I'm sorry, I've blown it one too many times.

20:33.041 --> 20:33.682
No, you haven't.

20:35.266 --> 20:36.187
Not in Jesus' eyes.

20:38.150 --> 20:45.759
In saying this to Peter, Jesus was making clear that he sees us, and I hope you'll get this, I hope you'll really pay attention to this one.

20:47.121 --> 20:54.470
He sees us in light of our future, not in light of our failure.

20:59.035 --> 21:04.562
Peter, I'm praying for you that your faith won't fail, but when you turn back,

21:04.930 --> 21:06.632
It's that past or future.

21:09.335 --> 21:11.937
When you turn back, is it past or future?

21:14.060 --> 21:16.162
The rest of you just failed, but it's not final.

21:16.222 --> 21:17.443
You'll recover, okay?

21:19.405 --> 21:19.946
It's future.

21:20.206 --> 21:23.950
When you turn back, strengthen your brothers.

21:26.112 --> 21:31.858
My problem is I have a hard time seeing my present or my future

21:33.058 --> 21:35.522
without seeing it through the lens of my failures.

21:38.746 --> 21:44.935
This is why I give up, this is why I stop trying, this is why I just lose it.

21:45.896 --> 21:54.368
Because I can't see a past of future because in the past, in moments like this, I kept failing.

21:55.931 --> 21:57.773
But Jesus doesn't see you through that lens.

21:59.416 --> 22:01.138
He sees you through the lens

22:01.314 --> 22:07.800
of what He can do in you and through you, not through the lens of what you've done without Him.

22:10.302 --> 22:13.365
In saying this to Peter, do you see why this is so important to me?

22:14.727 --> 22:15.728
Some of you are going, not really.

22:16.008 --> 22:17.890
Well, if you knew me, you'd see why.

22:20.432 --> 22:31.122
In saying this to Peter, Jesus was making clear that He will transform our failures from what they are, absolute negatives, destructive,

22:31.426 --> 22:36.073
to what they can be positive.

22:37.975 --> 22:41.861
And he can only do it if we respond properly.

22:42.141 --> 22:51.695
He wants to turn our failures from negatives to positives, but we have to respond in the appropriate way.

22:53.738 --> 22:57.303
Now, you have to notice that he's not saying that our failures are positive.

22:57.924 --> 22:59.346
Our failures are not positive.

23:02.306 --> 23:04.329
Our failures are absolutely negative.

23:05.590 --> 23:22.393
But what God can do is He can take those negative realities that we have brought into the world and He can turn them into a foundation of unbelievable positive impact because Jesus can walk right out of the tomb and be alive.

23:22.734 --> 23:24.076
We just have to see it.

23:24.196 --> 23:25.958
He can transform our lives.

23:26.619 --> 23:28.722
But we have to respond properly.

23:28.962 --> 23:30.284
Peter's a great example of this.

23:30.424 --> 23:32.887
Peter had just failed profoundly.

23:32.927 --> 23:39.115
And yet then the first day of the church, the day of Pentecost, comes when the Holy Spirit comes down.

23:39.215 --> 23:47.946
And you'll never guess who the one was that got to stand up and speak about the hope of Christ in the wake of his failures.

23:49.087 --> 23:49.608
It was Peter.

23:50.929 --> 23:56.917
Then Peter, in Acts chapter two, stood up with the 11 and raised his voice and addressed the crowd.

23:56.937 --> 23:57.938
Do you remember the verse?

23:58.274 --> 24:00.117
I'm praying that your faith will not fail.

24:01.078 --> 24:05.384
When you've turned back, strengthen the brothers.

24:07.887 --> 24:11.372
He's standing up in the midst of his brothers.

24:11.432 --> 24:12.754
And he's saying, we all blew it.

24:12.774 --> 24:13.535
We all failed.

24:13.715 --> 24:14.496
I blew it most.

24:14.857 --> 24:16.419
But Jesus is still real.

24:16.779 --> 24:18.161
His hope is still alive.

24:18.502 --> 24:20.264
And we need to share his love with the world.

24:20.304 --> 24:21.005
And so he did it.

24:21.045 --> 24:24.530
He stood up and he addressed the entire crowd this failure.

24:25.314 --> 24:29.558
They fellow Jews and all of you who live in Jerusalem, let me explain this event to you.

24:29.618 --> 24:31.741
Listen carefully to what I say.

24:31.841 --> 24:38.087
And he talked about the hope of Jesus, which prior to his denial, he didn't really understand.

24:40.149 --> 24:45.054
But after his denial, he knew the power of God's forgiveness.

24:46.656 --> 24:47.577
And he talked about it.

24:47.697 --> 24:52.722
And at the end, it says, those who accepted this failure's message

24:53.442 --> 24:57.046
were baptized, and about 3,000 were added to their number that day.

24:57.967 --> 25:02.612
Man, we look back at Peter with a halo on his head saying, man, what an awesome guy.

25:03.352 --> 25:03.933
No, he wasn't.

25:06.095 --> 25:09.018
But he served an awesome savior, and so do we.

25:09.619 --> 25:12.102
Our failures don't have to be final.

25:12.122 --> 25:17.708
God can transform the negative impact into positive reality, just like he did with Peter.

25:17.808 --> 25:20.050
And when Jesus said this to Peter,

25:20.450 --> 25:31.266
He was making clear to us that the only failure that is final, listen up, the only failure that is final is a failure of faith.

25:33.369 --> 25:39.858
This is why he said what he said, I'm praying that you don't lose your faith.

25:41.250 --> 25:42.912
I'm praying that your faith doesn't fail.

25:43.133 --> 25:43.914
It's going to waver.

25:43.974 --> 25:45.216
You're going to beat yourself up.

25:45.316 --> 25:46.097
It's going to be weak.

25:46.477 --> 25:46.878
I get it.

25:47.158 --> 25:59.516
But I'm praying that you don't have a failure of faith because your only hope for experiencing God's fullness is going to be found through the forgiveness that comes through faith.

26:00.918 --> 26:03.922
And as a pastor, I'm going to tell you, as a person who needs this myself,

26:04.258 --> 26:13.387
I am so sad that when people most need the forgiveness of Jesus, they throw away the only thing that can get them their faith.

26:13.747 --> 26:26.679
They run from God, they hide from God, they deny God, they get mad at God, and they leave God out of their lives, which leaves them in the pit of their own failure and guilt and darkness.

26:27.200 --> 26:30.303
And the only failure that's final is a failure of faith.

26:30.323 --> 26:32.124
Don't let yourself go there.

26:32.485 --> 26:33.906
Jesus is praying.

26:34.018 --> 26:35.620
that you won't lose your faith.

26:36.640 --> 26:47.070
John 3 18 says it, whoever has faith in him believes in him is not condemned, no matter what they've done.

26:48.832 --> 26:56.079
But whoever does not believe stands condemned already because they have not believed in the name of God's one and only son.

26:57.560 --> 27:01.464
The only failure that's final is the failure of faith.

27:02.405 --> 27:03.826
And I want to encourage you today

27:04.066 --> 27:05.188
Don't lose your faith.

27:06.089 --> 27:14.120
And if you have lost your faith, let God gift it back to you because this is what you need to find what you're longing for in life.

27:15.362 --> 27:18.726
So let me make this personal to you.

27:20.449 --> 27:24.134
What's the failure that's haunting you these days?

27:27.739 --> 27:32.786
I mean, what's the failure or failures that are weighing you down right now?

27:33.890 --> 27:40.201
that you can't see your life without seeing the destructive power of that failure.

27:40.882 --> 27:42.585
Have you failed in a relationship?

27:42.665 --> 27:44.688
Have you failed in a marriage?

27:44.748 --> 27:46.471
Have you failed with your kids?

27:47.613 --> 27:50.759
Have you failed with an issue of your character?

27:50.819 --> 27:52.722
Have you failed because of your

27:52.834 --> 28:04.632
inability to control your anger and your temper or your greed or you failed because of dishonesty or some kind of pursuit of sexual pleasure that's outside of God's destiny for you.

28:04.692 --> 28:07.316
I mean, what failures haunting you?

28:07.557 --> 28:12.024
Have you failed in worshiping Him like you've pretended to do?

28:12.064 --> 28:15.509
Have you failed in loving Him the way you know you ought?

28:15.549 --> 28:18.834
Have you failed in sharing Him as you should?

28:20.834 --> 28:27.941
As you know, from experience, the guilt of our failures fills our lives with all kinds of negatives.

28:29.563 --> 28:39.853
Regret, shame, darkness, and it robs us of the ability to enjoy all of God's promises.

28:41.895 --> 28:49.042
Guilt is for many a great bondage, a great torture, and a great prison.

28:50.882 --> 28:53.386
But he's already unlocked the prison door.

28:57.171 --> 28:59.074
You don't need him to sneak in a file.

29:01.758 --> 29:08.108
If you've ever been to the Pirates of the Caribbean, down in Disney World, you don't need to beg the doggy with the keys in his mouth to come.

29:11.713 --> 29:12.294
I enjoyed that.

29:12.354 --> 29:13.275
I don't know if you did or not.

29:13.295 --> 29:16.721
That was better than a latte right now for me.

29:16.921 --> 29:17.682
That was awesome.

29:20.194 --> 29:22.196
Jesus has already opened the door.

29:22.256 --> 29:29.644
If you're in the prison of guilt and regret and shame, it's because you keep choosing to live there.

29:30.105 --> 29:32.007
Your failures don't have to be final.

29:32.107 --> 29:38.273
You need to stand up and put your faith in Jesus Christ who died for you and rose again.

29:38.313 --> 29:40.856
Your failures don't have to be final.

29:45.401 --> 29:50.066
Now, in view of that truth, here's the vital question we're asking.

29:51.042 --> 29:53.045
What if it's true?

29:53.065 --> 30:02.419
I mean, I know we talk about it, but what if it's really true that our failures don't have to be final?

30:02.800 --> 30:06.946
That which holds us hostage doesn't have to keep us hostage anymore.

30:07.287 --> 30:09.270
It doesn't have to be the epitaph of our life.

30:09.570 --> 30:16.221
What if it's true that God is willing and able to forgive us of our failures?

30:16.561 --> 30:19.826
Well, if it's true, then

30:22.498 --> 30:23.539
it should change our lives.

30:27.102 --> 30:36.091
I just wanna share with you the answers to this, and then hopefully you, like me, will grapple with making them real in your life, okay?

30:38.573 --> 30:52.146
If it's true, and our failures don't have to be final in Jesus, then if we don't want our failures to define our lives, then, ooh, we should start here, we should start by faith to own up to our failures.

30:55.362 --> 30:56.544
we should own up to our failures.

30:57.505 --> 30:58.647
But that's not what we do, right?

30:59.348 --> 31:09.823
No, we hide them, we deny them, we create the image that we're better than we know we are, which makes us more lonely, more desperate and more broken.

31:12.227 --> 31:18.617
But he says, man, you don't have to cover your failures with layers of images.

31:20.399 --> 31:22.322
All you have to do is own up to them.

31:23.426 --> 31:26.090
Look what he said through John 1 John 1 9.

31:26.531 --> 31:34.784
If we confess our sins to him, he is faithful and just and will forgive us our sins and purify us from all unrighteousness.

31:37.087 --> 31:40.212
Own up to them or they're going to be final.

31:44.078 --> 31:48.185
A lot of people think that's exactly what people should do who don't know Jesus yet.

31:48.566 --> 31:51.410
The only problem is, while that is a true statement,

31:52.226 --> 31:55.049
This verse isn't for the people who don't know Jesus yet.

31:56.331 --> 32:05.382
This verse is written to people like us who are already followers of Jesus who still, like Peter, have this propensity to fail.

32:05.442 --> 32:11.049
And he says, hey, man, stop hiding it.

32:12.411 --> 32:15.875
Confess it so that I can forgive you for it.

32:17.337 --> 32:18.118
What if it's true?

32:18.298 --> 32:21.362
Well, if our failures don't really have to be final, then we should

32:22.114 --> 32:25.662
We should give our failures to Jesus by faith.

32:27.045 --> 32:27.927
Give them to Jesus.

32:29.911 --> 32:30.653
Here's the truth.

32:32.056 --> 32:40.114
We say we have, but we haven't because if we had given them to Jesus, we wouldn't still be holding on to them.

32:41.826 --> 32:44.831
If we had given them to Jesus, they wouldn't be defining our lives.

32:44.872 --> 32:46.595
They wouldn't be determining our choices.

32:46.635 --> 32:48.458
They wouldn't be causing us to back away.

32:48.839 --> 32:52.966
We wouldn't be working so hard to cover them up because we wouldn't even have them anymore.

32:54.649 --> 33:00.860
The only problem is we sing the songs, we talk the talk, but it's not true of us just like it wasn't true of Peter.

33:01.101 --> 33:04.427
We're still with Peter going, I'm such a profound Jesus follower.

33:04.868 --> 33:06.130
No, you're not.

33:08.322 --> 33:14.589
but he's a profound Jesus and all you have to do is give your junk to him and then it's gone.

33:15.010 --> 33:16.772
Your failures don't have to be final.

33:17.052 --> 33:18.073
They don't have to be.

33:19.035 --> 33:20.176
Give your failures to him.

33:21.437 --> 33:29.867
Acts chapter 20 verse 21, I have declared to both Jews and Greeks all of humanity that they must turn to God in our failures.

33:31.209 --> 33:32.210
We turn away from him.

33:33.090 --> 33:35.713
Hold on to them, try and cover them up, try and deal with them around.

33:36.034 --> 33:50.232
But if we're going to experience what Jesus came to give us, we must turn to God in repentance, which is a word of changing our mind, turning towards Him from being away from Him, and then have faith in our Lord Jesus.

33:50.692 --> 33:57.000
When Peter denied Jesus and saw his eyes, he's broken and he hid from Jesus.

33:58.963 --> 34:00.585
He said, I can't do this anymore, obviously.

34:00.605 --> 34:01.746
I'm just gonna go fishing.

34:02.850 --> 34:06.474
So Jesus chased him down and grabbed him by the lapels.

34:06.814 --> 34:12.300
No, he didn't, but he did chase him down and he said, you're forgiven.

34:16.544 --> 34:18.006
And that's what he's wanting to say to you.

34:22.470 --> 34:30.098
Give your failures to Jesus because when you let them go to him, you no longer have them.

34:34.626 --> 34:38.372
We have to entrust our failures and mistakes to Christ because He alone can forgive them.

34:38.412 --> 34:38.913
Think about this.

34:38.933 --> 34:46.546
There's nothing that you can do today or in the future that can change your past.

34:46.566 --> 34:54.399
We're trying to cover up with religion and we're trying to cover up with resolutions and we're trying to cover up with pledges and promises, and none of it removes our guilt.

34:54.780 --> 34:55.361
But know this.

34:55.721 --> 34:58.546
Jesus paid the full price of our guilt

34:58.626 --> 35:00.248
necessary to remove it.

35:00.628 --> 35:02.129
We don't deserve us forgiveness.

35:02.189 --> 35:04.892
We can't earn us forgiveness, but we can receive it.

35:05.192 --> 35:05.593
Have you?

35:09.496 --> 35:12.659
What if it's true if our failures don't have to be final in Jesus?

35:12.699 --> 35:21.528
Well, then once we've confessed our failures to Him and given our failures to Him, then we must by faith, and this is the hard part for me.

35:23.029 --> 35:28.434
Then we must by faith refuse to let our failures

35:28.578 --> 35:29.339
define us.

35:31.481 --> 35:32.262
This is really hard.

35:35.505 --> 35:41.030
It's exactly what Romans 6 says in talking about how to get free from all of our failures and junk in the name of Jesus.

35:42.091 --> 35:44.694
It says in the same way, you have to do something that doesn't come natural.

35:45.394 --> 35:57.586
Once you've confessed to Jesus and given your failures to Jesus, you need to count yourselves dead to sin that no longer defines you, but alive to God in Christ Jesus.

35:59.970 --> 36:01.452
You need to count this to be true.

36:04.716 --> 36:06.158
I never feel like it's true.

36:07.780 --> 36:08.521
You know what I feel like?

36:09.222 --> 36:09.662
A failure?

36:11.084 --> 36:11.885
You know what I feel like?

36:14.648 --> 36:17.772
The last failure of my life, which wasn't long ago?

36:19.334 --> 36:20.035
That's what I feel like.

36:20.796 --> 36:21.377
Not how you feel?

36:22.758 --> 36:23.379
Come on, be honest.

36:27.985 --> 36:28.946
But he didn't say,

36:29.986 --> 36:36.353
He said, he didn't say, Peter, I'm praying for you that your feelings don't fail you.

36:37.835 --> 36:50.348
He said, I'm praying that your faith won't fail you because in spite of how you feel and what everyone else says about you, you need to know that in Jesus Christ, you are no longer defined by sin.

36:50.429 --> 36:55.674
You are defined by the life of God in you and you need to go out and live that life in fullness.

36:55.754 --> 36:59.058
You need to know your failures are not final.

37:00.450 --> 37:02.213
But again, this is really hard for me.

37:02.433 --> 37:06.159
So I had to find a key, and remember this is for me, I'm just sharing it with you.

37:06.439 --> 37:07.160
I had to find a key.

37:07.220 --> 37:10.666
What do I hold on to when I'm feeling like the failure I know I am?

37:11.567 --> 37:12.348
What do I hold on to?

37:12.509 --> 37:13.330
Here's what I hold on to.

37:13.911 --> 37:19.780
I take God at His word in spite of how I feel.

37:19.820 --> 37:23.826
Take God at His word in spite of how you feel.

37:25.090 --> 37:27.132
And so here's what you have to do.

37:27.312 --> 37:28.894
You have to know what God said.

37:29.134 --> 37:32.237
So let me just give you a couple of things that he said that helped me, okay?

37:34.299 --> 37:40.585
God says that he removes the stain of our sin and failures.

37:40.625 --> 37:41.345
That's what God says.

37:42.106 --> 37:48.532
He says, in Jesus, when you come to me, I remove the stain of your sin and failures.

37:49.213 --> 37:54.738
Now right there calls for a metaphor about laundry, right?

37:55.778 --> 38:06.154
I mean, it should be a tide commercial or a gain commercial or something like that, how you had a stain and spray it with shout, and the stain's gone, whoo, save my clothing.

38:06.455 --> 38:07.656
It calls for that metaphor.

38:07.957 --> 38:18.193
The only problem, if I gave you a metaphor about laundry, my wife would phone in and say he's a laia, he doesn't know anything about laundry.

38:18.213 --> 38:19.194
So I can't do it.

38:19.214 --> 38:24.082
And another thing is, I have done laundry, but those clothes were destroyed.

38:24.322 --> 38:32.435
Laundry and me don't get along, but this, He removes our sin and our failures and the stain they cause.

38:33.176 --> 38:36.822
Isaiah 1, 18, come now, let us reason together, says who?

38:37.984 --> 38:38.605
Let's do that again.

38:38.905 --> 38:40.367
Come now, let us reason together.

38:40.588 --> 38:41.409
Failure's not final.

38:41.429 --> 38:42.931
I'm going to give you another chance, okay?

38:43.613 --> 38:49.161
Come now, let us reason together, says, not me, not religion.

38:49.221 --> 38:50.964
The Lord says this.

38:51.144 --> 38:52.146
The Lord says this.

38:53.250 --> 38:58.455
Though your sins are filled with the stain of scarlet, they shall be white as snow.

38:58.756 --> 39:04.902
Though they are red as crimson, they shall be like wool."

39:04.922 --> 39:06.604
He says he removes the stain of our sin.

39:06.864 --> 39:09.086
How come I keep feeling the stain of my sin?

39:09.547 --> 39:11.048
Because I'm not taking him at his word.

39:11.408 --> 39:12.149
You know what else he says?

39:12.429 --> 39:15.613
He says that he forgets our sin and failures.

39:17.254 --> 39:17.755
Isn't it weird?

39:18.235 --> 39:20.818
We remember them so much that they

39:20.898 --> 39:25.865
determine our choices and mess up our lives, but he forgets our sin and failures.

39:25.885 --> 39:32.735
Look what he says through Jeremiah, 31, 34 and 35, for I will forgive their wickedness, not their little teeny little sins.

39:34.618 --> 39:39.325
I will forgive their wickedness and will remember their sins no more.

39:39.705 --> 39:43.090
This is what says.

39:45.858 --> 39:47.340
Am I going to believe what I feel?

39:47.460 --> 39:48.822
Or am I going to believe what he says?

39:48.903 --> 39:50.104
Well, here's the problem.

39:50.124 --> 39:53.349
When I believe what I feel, I always do the wrong thing.

39:53.389 --> 40:00.941
But when I believe what he says, I can live the life that only he can make possible.

40:01.281 --> 40:02.303
What are you believing?

40:02.343 --> 40:03.705
Are you taking him at his word?

40:04.025 --> 40:04.987
Take him at his word.

40:05.708 --> 40:06.569
And one last one.

40:07.330 --> 40:08.252
This is what he says.

40:08.833 --> 40:13.319
He says he gives us a clean slate from our sin and failure in Jesus.

40:14.281 --> 40:15.122
Clean slate.

40:15.394 --> 40:15.915
I don't know about you.

40:16.255 --> 40:17.136
I feel like that.

40:17.456 --> 40:23.783
Have you ever seen those whiteboards that someone didn't use erasable markers on?

40:25.946 --> 40:27.047
That's what I feel like in life.

40:29.289 --> 40:30.531
But that's not how he sees me.

40:32.212 --> 40:36.197
2 Corinthians 5, 17, therefore if anyone is in Christ, he's a new creation.

40:37.578 --> 40:39.801
The old has gone, the new has come.

40:41.683 --> 40:44.626
God recreates us, makes us new.

40:45.602 --> 40:55.337
Isn't it sad that I ruin the new life that God has given me by living the old life that he's taken from me?

40:57.059 --> 40:57.760
And you do too.

40:59.222 --> 41:05.952
We need to start taking him at his word, which is why he says this, Peter, I'm praying that your faith doesn't fail.

41:07.535 --> 41:08.516
Look, I know you blew it.

41:09.458 --> 41:10.219
I know you failed.

41:11.120 --> 41:11.941
I know it's hard.

41:12.602 --> 41:13.684
I know it's agonizing.

41:14.385 --> 41:15.026
I relate.

41:16.674 --> 41:23.541
but you can't let that keep you from trusting Him because He knew you were going to fail.

41:23.601 --> 41:25.222
He loves you anyway.

41:26.624 --> 41:34.651
He doesn't see your failures as final and He's just waiting for you to come back to Him so He can do in you what you long for Him to do.

41:35.192 --> 41:37.314
You need to take Him at His Word.

41:37.634 --> 41:42.258
And then when you do, it changes everything.

41:43.540 --> 41:46.002
When you've experienced His forgiveness,

41:46.530 --> 41:48.537
for your betrayal, like Peter did.

41:49.018 --> 41:50.363
Do you know what you do then?

41:50.443 --> 41:51.166
What if it's true?

41:51.447 --> 41:53.734
What if it's true that my failures are not final?

41:53.915 --> 41:59.634
Then, if it's really true, I should forgive others.

42:04.578 --> 42:12.366
Look at Ephesians 4.32, says, be kind and compassionate to one another, forgiving each other, justice and Christ God forgave you.

42:12.726 --> 42:19.112
Do you know what the natural outcome of experiencing his genuous, for genuine forgiveness is?

42:19.472 --> 42:23.476
The natural outcome is that I'm gonna wanna forgive others.

42:25.558 --> 42:28.902
Which is the problem with the Church of Jesus Christ.

42:31.144 --> 42:32.685
There's a lot of hatred in the church, isn't it?

42:32.906 --> 42:33.426
That's sad.

42:33.698 --> 42:34.539
I've experienced some of it.

42:36.641 --> 42:37.442
You know your own heart.

42:39.725 --> 42:43.048
It's easy to pray for people who are being good to you.

42:43.088 --> 42:47.373
It's easy to forget people who aren't.

42:50.376 --> 42:51.437
But that's vengeance.

42:51.537 --> 42:52.258
That's getting back.

42:52.539 --> 42:54.941
Let me tell you the reality of my life, see if you can relate.

42:55.822 --> 42:59.346
When I'm carrying guilt, I can't give people forgiveness.

43:00.962 --> 43:03.645
I can only give them the anger I deserve.

43:06.109 --> 43:07.871
Do you know why we have a hard time forgiving others?

43:07.951 --> 43:10.734
Because we're not really experiencing the forgiveness of Jesus.

43:14.980 --> 43:15.861
We need to forgive others.

43:19.786 --> 43:29.138
That's why Jesus said, pray this way, God forgive me my debts as I forgive those who are my debtors.

43:30.242 --> 43:30.522
Why?

43:30.542 --> 43:34.248
Because if you're forgiven, you can't help but be forgiving.

43:35.630 --> 43:42.000
So I've come up with three words in a phrase that can help you remember.

43:42.060 --> 43:44.584
You need to be forgiving others if this is really true.

43:44.644 --> 43:56.422
And there are words that I have a hard time saying out loud because I have eight grandchildren and I have lived through the era of grandchildren in the wake of Disney's Frozen.

43:57.444 --> 43:59.026
And I'm gonna tell you, I mean,

44:01.186 --> 44:05.750
Either I have obsessive grandchildren or kids are all obsessive.

44:05.770 --> 44:08.173
They want to watch it a billion times.

